# Trilemma Foundation Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack 
- **Frontend**: React 19.0.0, TypeScript 5.5.3, Vite 7.0.0, React Router v7.8.2
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3.4.13 with custom UI kit preset
- **Linting & Formatting**: Biome 2.3.10 (replaces ESLint + Prettier)
- **Hosting**: Vercel (static site)
- **Data**: Google Sheets CSV export, Google Docs embeds

## Project Structure

```
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── layout/        # PageLayout, Header, Footer, TwoColumnSection
│   │   ├── pages/
│   │   │   ├── landing/   # Landing page (Hero, UniversityMarquee, ProofOfPerformance)
│   │   │   ├── legal/     # Privacy, Terms pages
│   │   │   ├── projects/  # Projects table with Google Sheets data
│   │   │   ├── resources/ # Embedded Google Docs viewer
│   │   │   ├── team/      # Team directors page
│   │   │   └── tournaments/ # Tournament info and winners
│   │   └── UI/            # Reusable components (Button, StatusBadge, Section, etc.)
│   ├── hooks/             # Custom React hooks (useProjectsData, useBodyScrollLock)
│   ├── constants/         # Navigation, external links, university data (community.json)
│   ├── assets/            # Static images (logos, headshots)
│   └── types/             # Frontend-specific type declarations
├── public/                # Favicons and static assets
└── tailwind-ui-kit.preset.ts  # Design system tokens
```

## Routes

| Route | Component | Description |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| `/` | Landing | Hero, university marquee, proof of performance |
| `/projects` | Projects | Sortable/filterable table from Google Sheets |
| `/tournaments` | Tournaments | Current/past tournaments with winners |
| `/team` | Team | Directors with bios and LinkedIn |
| `/resources` | Resources | Embedded Google Docs with fullscreen |
| `/privacy` | Privacy | Privacy policy |
| `/terms` | Terms | Terms and conditions |

## Coding Conventions

### Linting & Formatting (Biome)
- Use Biome for both linting and formatting
- Run `npm run lint` to check for issues
- Run `npm run lint:fix` to auto-fix linting issues
- Run `npm run format` to format all files
- Run `npm run check` to run both lint and format checks
- Configuration: `biome.json` with recommended rules
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Double quotes for strings (formatter enforces this)
- 2-space indentation (formatter enforces this)

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode (`strict: true` in tsconfig)
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases
- Prefer explicit return types on exported functions

### React Components
- Use functional components with `React.FC<Props>` typing
- Define props interfaces inline above component
- Export components as default
- File naming: PascalCase matching component name
- Use `memo()` for expensive components (see TournamentsWinners, TeamDirectors)

```tsx
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}

const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ title, onClick }) => {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{title}</button>;
};

export default Component;
```

### Custom Hooks
- Prefix with `use` (e.g., `useProjectsData`, `useBodyScrollLock`)
- Return object with named properties: `{ data, loading, error }`
- Handle loading/error states internally

```tsx
// Data fetching hook pattern
export const useProjectsData = () => {
  const [projects, setProjects] = useState<Project[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  
  // ... fetch logic
  
  return { projects, loading, error };
};

// Utility hook pattern
export const useBodyScrollLock = (isLocked: boolean): void => {
  useEffect(() => {
    if (isLocked) {
      document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
    } else {
      document.body.style.overflow = "";
    }
    return () => { document.body.style.overflow = ""; };
  }, [isLocked]);
};
```

## Styling

### Tailwind Conventions
- Use design tokens from `tailwind-ui-kit.preset.ts`
- Semantic colors: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`
- Brand colors: `brand-navy`, `brand-orange`, `brand-amber`, `brand-blue`, `brand-white`
- Responsive prefixes: `xs:`, `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Touch targets: `min-h-touch` (44px), `touch-manipulation`

### Component Styling Pattern
```tsx
const baseStyles = 'rounded-lg transition-all';
const variantStyles = 'bg-brand-blue text-foreground';
const stateStyles = disabled ? 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed' : 'cursor-pointer';

return <button className={`${baseStyles} ${variantStyles} ${stateStyles}`} />;
```

## Best Practices

### Do
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract repeated logic into custom hooks
- Use early returns for loading/error states
- Colocate related files (component + its styles/types)
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations in render
- Use lazy loading for route components (see App.tsx)
- Use `loading="lazy"` and `decoding="async"` on images

### Don't
- Mix business logic with UI components
- Ignore TypeScript errors (fix them)
- Ignore Biome linting/formatting errors (run `npm run lint:fix` and `npm run format`)
- Store sensitive data in frontend state

### File Organization
- Pages: One directory per feature (`pages/landing/`, `pages/projects/`)
- Components: Group by function (`UI/`, `layout/`)
- Hooks: One hook per file in `hooks/`
- Constants: Centralized in `constants/` (navigation.ts, externalLinks.ts, community.json)

### Performance
- Use `React.memo()` sparingly for expensive components
- Pagination for large data sets (see `ProjectsTable`)
- Lazy load routes (all routes use React.lazy in App.tsx)
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include width/height attributes
- Use CSS visibility toggle for tab switching (see ResourcesTabs)

### External Data Integration
- Google Sheets: Fetch CSV via public export URL, parse with custom `parseCSV` function
- Google Docs: Embed via iframe with published document URL
- External forms: Link to Google Forms for enrollment
